cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.SC 

The paper discusses randomized algorithms for distributed computation of principal component analysis and singular value decomposition, which are commonly used in machine learning and data analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the use of these algorithms in improving the performance of Spark, a popular platform for distributed computation, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of numerical methods and optimization techniques in the algorithms could also place it in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.SC (Scientific Computing).
